modules.description: Processes ANSI escape codes from text streams, extracting and converting color and style information into HTML equivalents. It handles sequences for text color, background, and basic styling, producing styled output suitable for web display. Used to sanitize build logs and other terminal output for presentation in web-based interfaces.

Parses ANSI escape sequences from input strings, converting them into styled HTML output while preserving partial sequences across multiple calls. Works with raw string data and maintains internal state to handle incomplete sequences. Generates colored HTML output using predefined CSS themes or allows custom styling.
